The paper focuses on detecting anomaly behaviors in large-scale Internet topology, which involves network crashes and intentional attacks. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a method for anomaly detection using complex network path changes coefficient, which involves analyzing structured datasets and complex networks. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) categories. The paper also mentions the use of a decision function inspired by Fibonacci Sequence, which involves mathematical algorithms and data structures. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Information Theory (cs.IT) categories.
